reviews.review_text: 4-14-84 Good show. Real good Charlie Miller remaster.

Incredible Drums Space These are the years where things started to get a little dark...crack and blow in major circulation, and things seem to start getting strange from '84-'86...I would not see my first show until 3/26/87 but I was listening for a while and having listened- AND LOVED- this dark period of trippy dead music where Jerry's health was questionable all the time, I feel it had a significant effect on the music- IMHO. I am not expert but I love this show. The morning Dew is well done and the echoe of Garias Haunting lyrics and the texture to his vocals is pure symphony to me. The sound quality is top knotch and does not dissappoint at any level- JG is high in the mix-vocals are even, normalized and the band is into it! But its Hampton so of course it was a killer show! The previous night is one fo my favorite scarlet>fires...but this show has strong attitude- enjoy it! 5 stars baby!
